Axis Description Default Value x Negative X axis extends down. Positive X Axis extends up. 0 y Negative Y axis extends down. Positive Y Axis extends up. 0 z Negative Z axis extends in. Positive Z Axis extends out. 0 <pre><code>&lt;!-- x y z --&gt;
&lt;a-entity position="0 1 -1"&gt;&lt;/a-entity&gt;
</code></pre>

Example of a modified sky  <p>Create the file <code>skyGradient.js</code> and add the code:</p> <pre><code>/* global AFRAME */
AFRAME.registerShader('skyGradient', {
  schema: {
    colorTop: { type: 'color', default: 'black', is: 'uniform' },
    colorBottom: { type: 'color', default: 'red', is: 'uniform' }
  },

  vertexShader: [
    'varying vec3 vWorldPosition;',

    'void main() {',

      'vec4 worldPosition = modelMatrix * vec4( position, 1.0 );',
      'vWorldPosition = worldPosition.xyz;',

      'gl_Position = projectionMatrix * modelViewMatrix * vec4( position, 1.0 );',

    '}'

  ].join('\n'),

  fragmentShader: [
    'uniform vec3 colorTop;',
    'uniform vec3 colorBottom;',

    'varying vec3 vWorldPosition;',

    'void main()',

    '{',
      'vec3 pointOnSphere = normalize(vWorldPosition.xyz);',
      'float f = 1.0;',
      'if(pointOnSphere.y &gt; - 0.2){',

        'f = sin(pointOnSphere.y * 2.0);',

      '}',
      'gl_FragColor = vec4(mix(colorBottom,colorTop, f ), 1.0);',

    '}'
  ].join('\n')
});
</code></pre> <p>Then add the file and environment to index.html.</p> <p><pre><code>&lt;!-- dans le head --&gt;
&lt;script src="/skyGradient.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;!-- dans le body --&gt;
&lt;a-entity
  id="sky"
  geometry="primitive: sphere; radius: 65;"
  material="shader: skyGradient; colorTop: #353449; colorBottom: #BC483E; side: back"
&gt;&lt;/a-entity&gt;
</code></pre> Full code for the exemple:</p> Code <pre><code>&lt;html&gt;
    &lt;head&gt;
        &lt;script src="https://aframe.io/releases/1.7.1/aframe.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
        &lt;script src="/skyGradient.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;/head&gt;
    &lt;body&gt;
        &lt;a-scene&gt;
            &lt;a-entity id="sky" geometry="primitive: sphere; radius: 65;"
                material="shader: skyGradient; colorTop: #353449; colorBottom: #BC483E; side: back"&gt;&lt;a-entity&gt;
                    &lt;a-sphere position="0 1.25 -5" radius="1.25" color="#CCCCCC"&gt;&lt;/a-sphere&gt;
        &lt;/a-scene&gt;
    &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</code></pre>
